259	twitter	twitter_gitcoin	Author: gitcoin\nTweet: Coalitional funding: a 2026+ primitive 🤝\n\nThe difference between fragmented funding and funding that compounds? Sometimes it's not the mechanism – it's the coalition.\n\nSEMATECH, the Global Fund, and @linuxfoundation proved it. @ethereum brought it onchain.\n\nExamples:\n\n- @protocolguild solved the free-rider issue for Ethereum core contributors, no single sponsor needed\n\n- @ethereumfndn, @uniswap, @yearnfi, and others pooled tens of millions via quadratic funding rounds to support public goods\n\nAs capital allocation becomes more plural and programmable, coalitional funding is how the onchain ecosystem coordinates at scale 💚\n\n@owocki and @griffgreen go deeper 👇\n🔗 https://t.co/DzWj6AOEwR\nLinks: https://gitcoin.co/research/coalitional-funding-2026-era-primitive\nSource kind: account	https://x.com/gitcoin/status/2029744072613843320	https://x.com/gitcoin/status/2029744072613843320	2ec2facbec94b03c9855137180a4a8a0041e8a616ce3044da9fcd3ce108f6e63	2026-07-03 03:15:51.119755+00
