1052	twitter	twitter_optimism	Author: Optimism\nTweet: Get caught up with the latest from the Superchain ecosystem in &lt;2 mins 👇\nQuoted tweet: Here’s everything that happened across the Superchain ecosystem this past week.\n\n🧪 @SuccinctLabs is partnering with @Optimism to bring ZK to the Superchain. OP Succinct will become a preferred ZK proving solution, with OP Mainnet set to integrate in the coming months\n🔴 ERC-8004 is now live on OP Mainnet, introducing identity, reputation, and validation registries for trustless AI agents. 10,000+ agents registered on testnet ahead of mainnet launch\n📊 @MessariCrypto released the State of the Superchain H2’25 report shows 3.6B total transactions (ATH), 12.7% of total crypto activity, and $1.95B in active loans (+95.8% YoY)\n🔐 @OPLabsPBC released a new open-source liveness module for multisigs, designed to prevent key-loss failures and strengthen treasury security\n⚙️ OP Stack Upgrade 18 (U18) is live, improving performance, flexibility, and operational efficiency across the Superchain\n🦙 @_Llamaswap is now live on @inkonchain, routing trades across aggregators for better execution with no added fees\n🌪️ @nadoHQ raised its NLP deposit cap to $4M, expanding Alpha Tornado and Storm tier capacity\n💿 @soneium launched Season 07, welcoming Arkada, CapnCompany, Sake Finance, and the upcoming Startale App\n🎮 @record_protocol secured $3.2M from @Sony Innovation Fund to scale onchain entertainment toward IPFi\n📈 @OrderlyNetwork surpassed 1M unique walletsk\n⬜️ @worldcoin is running a trusted setup ceremony for the next version of World ID, strengthening ZK security guarantees\n🌏@Lisk highlighted on/off-ramps as the next major adoption bottleneck, pointing to fragmented infrastructure and hidden costs as the real constraint\n🖥️ @JANCTION_Global partnered with @swan_chain to expand its decentralized GPU cloud capacity, unlocking access to ~25,000 compute resources for scalable AI, rendering, and high-performance workloads\n🧩 @DeriveX