1530	twitter	twitter_gitcoin	Author: gitcoin\nTweet: Deep Funding is where experimentation meets execution.\n\nA $350K market-driven funding model for Ethereum infra - part of #GG24.\n\nIncredible work from @devanshmehta and the team👇\nQuoted tweet: here's the results from the trial run of @deep_funding  to derive weights b/w 45 repos part of @argotorg , @ProtocolGuild  & @devtoolsguild 👀\n\nit's scary to distribute $350,000 without a test drive first, so im glad we finished a trial before the @gitcoin GG24 Deep Funding round commences 😌\n\nIf you want your ethereum web3 infra or dev tooling based repo to participate, simply fill up a google form with your repo url and TG handle (link in replies)\n\nnow, onto analysis of the results;\n\nleft image (L) - from the (offchain) @JoinPond data science contest contest, used to determine the 45-50 new repos eligible to receive money in GG24\n\nright image (R) - from the (onchain) @seer_pm prediction market used in GG24 to determine split of funds b/w accepted 90-100 repos in the round\n\n(poll for you to vote on which split is better in replies)\n\nsome observations\n\n-  L is more uniform in its distribution compared to R, where there is a relatively sharp cutoff after geth. markets do reward power law outcomes after all 😅\n\n-  just off  its ordering, R is a bit more on how fundamental the projects are while L seems to rank  on outreach/practical transformativity. for eg, it puts foundry over solidity, which maybe doesn't make sense from a fundamental/dependency point of view?\n\n- R ranks experimental programming languages like fe & act over vyper, which doesn't feel right\n\n- 25 deep funding jurors out of 50 voted on their preference between L & R; 2/3rd preferred the split in R while 1/3rd liked L better\n\nGG24 Deep Funding begins October 20th to distribute $350,000. Here's how to participate\n\n- Apply before October 17th if you are a project and receive funds before Devconnect\n\n- Bet on a repos value from from October 20th to November 5th to earn money if you are a trader\n\n- Become a juror whose comparisons between repos help resolve the market, if you are an open source evaluator\n\n& commit to funding these repos based on their market derived weights if you are an ethereum supporter!\nSource kind: account	https://x.com/gitcoin/status/1977826697799139580	https://x.com/gitcoin/status/1977826697799139580	daf5a525608154a20c249f2ce16b39195355d6a6066d8fd196250e0e0e06c97d	2026-07-03 06:03:13.056411+00
