1569	twitter	twitter_suinetwork	Author: SuiNetwork\nTweet: This is what a real merchant layer looks like.\n\nPay with any token. Fees upfront. Clean settlement. All on Sui.\nQuoted tweet: Sui was built for payments.\n\nCoinVoyage makes that usable for merchants.\n\nBuyers can pay with the token they already hold:\nThis removes the need for buyers to start with a specific asset before checkout. The payment flow begins with the token they already have, making the experience more flexible and easier to complete.\n\nRouting happens across the required infrastructure:\nBehind the scenes, the transaction moves through the infrastructure needed to complete the payment flow on Sui. Routing, bridging, and settlement work together in the background so the front-end experience stays simple.\n\nFees are shown before confirmation:\nTransaction costs are visible before the buyer approves the payment. That gives users a clearer view of total cost at checkout and adds more transparency before confirmation.\n\nExecution stays non-custodial:\nThe payment flow is designed to execute without CoinVoyage taking custody of user funds. Users remain in control of their assets throughout the transaction while still getting a streamlined experience.\n\nSettlement reaches the destination cleanly.\n\nFor @SuiNetwork, that means a merchant payment flow built for real-world use, not just chain-level speed.\n\nWatch the full launch video below.\n\nLive now at https://t.co/Q7jlkYlTzh\nSource kind: account	https://x.com/SuiNetwork/status/2042367679601000517	https://x.com/SuiNetwork/status/2042367679601000517	ec9cc420747b7cc9a2ef480c080773845c2810dfbaba464c45f3d51e466903a6	2026-07-03 06:03:13.110953+00
