1833	twitter	twitter_optimism	Author: Optimism\nTweet: As the industry grows, each layer is taking on its own role. For Optimism, that means building a foundation for enterprises by delivering scalable, reliable, and configurable blockspace for institutions bringing the next wave of products onchain.\nQuoted tweet: "Do L2s compete with Ethereum?" I get this question a lot (understandably).\n\nThe reality is that it depends. The relationship between ETH and L2s sits in an extremely weird spot. L2s are somewhere between a customer, a partner, an employee, and a competitor. \n\nOne of the things it depends on is how you define "compete". Do you mean:\n\nAre L2s and ETH playing a zero sum game for revenue? No. Many people prefer to build their apps on Ethereum - it's lindy, it has the most liquidity, and has the best devtool + integration support. App builders deploy elsewhere if their product doesn't work within the latency and cost constraints of L1. And if all else equal, they pick the blockspace where they get the best GTM support (eg Jesse from Base).\n\nAre L2s and ETH playing a zero sum game for marketshare? Marketshare is "percentage of total sales within your industry". Crypto is still defining its market right now. Optimism is creating an enterprise market and selling customizable blockspace for financial institutions to deploy their next wave of products. Our focus is scale, reliability, configurability. What is Ethereum's offering and who are they selling it to? I'd argue that focusing on L2s as a core customer group + building a secure settlement layer is the most advantageous thing for Ethereum to do.\n\nAs the market for crypto gets bigger, and everyone begins to specialize more, relationships between companies will also become more clear. When the pie is not growing, these relationships can become more complicated. The same thing happens inside of startups - when the market is down or the business isn't doing well, everything is a problem. Everybody sucks, politics abound, the CEO is a twat... Winning fixes a lot of problems. So... let's get to work ❤️\nSource kind: account	https://x.com/Optimism/status/1995825882888372672	https://x.com/Optimism/status/1995825882888372672	e0c6550628048b5a8b65ec5a3dae22fe6254cb0d0990053e2639e1fa29607411	2026-07-03 07:00:17.688981+00
